content.description: This route starts in an obvious open book before traversing the smooth, right side wall to the corner then up and around the large roof. Interesting, sustained 5.7 climbing past two bolts and eventually to the top. A 60m rope just made it down in one rap.
content.protection: G - Good gear abounds and two bolts protect an area which would otherwise offer no protection.
content.location: Toward the left side of the North End area there is an obvious open book capped with a large roof. Usually marked with a large amount of bird crap from nesting crows.

content.description: Large wall with a number of large roofs and dramatic faces. Reminded me of the Near Trapps in the Gunks.
